  "texts": [
    "Additionally, Decision Tree (DT) and Support Vector Machine (SVM) are popular choices, featured in 8 and 9 studies, respectively.",
    "Furthermore, K-Nearest Neighbor (KNN), Extreme Gradient Boosting (XGBoost), Naive Bayes (NB), and Logistic Regression are each present in 6, 6, 5, and 2 studies, respectively.",
    "Additionally, clustering models are featured in 1 study, where contracts are grouped by creator addresses to identify different versions by the same developers and match destructed contracts to later \"upgraded\" versions based on similarity.",
    "In addition, Table 7 presents an overview of the prevalence of deep learning models in primary studies.",
    "Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN) emerge as the most utilized recurrent model, found in 9 studies, followed by Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) with 7 occurrences."
  ]
}